result.execSummary:
The defendant Delisa Michelle Curtis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Prostitution-Nonmmarital Sexual Intercourse [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 944.30(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: May transfer to Milwaukee County.  1 day credit if revoked.

miscConds.notes:
Costs waived by the Court.

The Defendant is to undergo any counseling the agent finds appropriate and must comply with any recommended treatment/assessment/counseling.  The Defendant is to have no contact with backpage.com.  The Court allows early discharge after 6 months if she is doing well.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.
